# ---- Production environment variables (copy to Render dashboard) ----
# Render auto-sets: PORT, RENDER_EXTERNAL_URL (used as CLIENT_URL automatically).

# Required:
NODE_ENV=production

# MongoDB Atlas connection string (M0 free tier). Required.
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://USER:PASS@cluster.xxxxx.mongodb.net/attendance-system?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# 32+ char random strings. Generate each with:
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
JWT_SECRET=replace-with-a-long-random-hex-string
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=replace-with-a-long-random-hex-string
QR_CODE_SECRET=replace-with-a-long-random-hex-string

# Optional: only set if the SPA is served from a DIFFERENT domain than the API.
# When deployed as a single Render service this is unnecessary (auto-filled
# from RENDER_EXTERNAL_URL).
# CLIENT_URL=https://your-custom-domain.com

# --- Demo geofence for seeded sessions (optional) ---
# If you plan to test QR attendance from a real phone, set these to YOUR
# current GPS coordinates and a generous radius so scans pass.
# (The frontend sends the phone's real GPS; the session must be within
#  radius meters of it.) Leave unset to use the Bangalore default (100m).
# SEED_GEOFENCE_LAT=12.9716
# SEED_GEOFENCE_LON=77.5946
# SEED_GEOFENCE_RADIUS=500

# --- Frontend build-time vars (baked into the bundle by Vite) ---
# Defaults are same-origin, which is correct for a single-service deploy.
# Only override if splitting frontend/backend onto different hosts.
# VITE_API_URL=/api
# VITE_SOCKET_URL=https://your-api-domain.com
